3>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>4:02:42 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.3snip.com/eliteforce/images/coatie.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First of all, GREAT job on the Raid last night in Tower of Frozen Shadow!  everyone was listening very well and turned out to be very successful raid, until we lost Yuedar of course <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...<br>
<br>
However, there is one thing that Xunil, Naroon, and I have discussed that we feel should be addressed.  <br>
<br>
We had a bit of a conflict with another guild last night.  On the fourth floor of tower, there is a rare spawn named Cara that drops the key to the 5th floor plus some really expensive loot as well.  She takes a lot of work and time to make her spawn, and the other guild was working to do this.  The elites stumbled upon her room, and she was up and no one was in the room.  We had not called a camp check prior, assumed that she was not camped, and proceeded to kill her.  While we were fighting, the other guild came in, and one member of that guild was very harsh to us right as he entered  the room.  It was clear that they were running around on the 4th floor, trying to get her to spawn, and we happened to be in the room before they had a chance to get back.<br>
<br>
Now, I am sure that if the other guild came in the room and acted politely, explaining their situation, everything would have turned out all right.  We did not NEED the 5th floor key, as we already had one in each group.  However, the other guild came in and started to use foul and harsh language, which in turn incited many of our guild members into saying just as harsh things.  <br>
<br>
The end result was that I looted the key (there was no loot) after trying to offer it to them (They refused to take it for whatever reason).  The point that we would like to make is twofold.  First, on any dungeon raid, even if we intend to &quot;do&quot; the dungeon as ooposed to camping something, we should always do a camp check before we take a step in so we do not step on other groups' toes.  Second, if some &quot;punk&quot; starts to yell at us and use foul language, the proper response from us should be that of an understanding and &quot;lets work this out like adults&quot; tone.  We should never lash back at them and sink to their level.  If you feel that you must let out your frustration, do so in the confines of your group or guild chat (without foul language of course) as to not cause more conflict.<br>
<br>
It is understandable that people do get upset after being lashed at, however, as Elites, we should always present ourselves as Honorable, Courageous, and Compassionate people.  Tempers will flare, mouths will foam, however, keep it within the guildchat or groupchat, and conflicts with others outside our family should remain at a low.  <br>
<br>
I spoke with the leader of the other guild after the incident, he profusely apologized for the group's behavior, saying of course that it was NOT necessary for them to lash out at us that way.  However, I did apologize for the Elites as well, for we should have been courteous of other people in the zone that may have been camping something also.  True, if it is not engaged, it is open, but this spawn in particular is hard to spawn and requires you to not be in the room at all times.  Lets keep that in mind next time and hopefully we'll have even MORE fun with no conflicts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Always be courteous and understanding of others and treat them as if they were an Elite also.  We don't want to present ourselves in a manner to which people perceive us as Mean, KSers and Harsh people.  Thank you for reading, if you got this far that is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Feel free to comment, send me an email or whatever.  Comments on this are appreciated if you have any.  Thanks Elites and See you in Norrath!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><IMG SRC="http://www.3snip.com/eliteforce/images/coatie-sig.gif"<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#A8A8A8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/btheeliteforce.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lorelahnabrytblade>LoreLahna Brytblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.bellsnwhistles.com/aspi/1asp141.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Nature's Queen</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>24</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>4:17:46 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.home.net/gnddituri/images/lore1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Coatie, I totally agree.  Harsh language never solves the problem but it takes both parties acting in adult fashion and unfortunately that is not always the case.  I know we try to always do a camp check, but on the flip side of that, people don't always respond.  I have run into that problem a couple of times and there is not much you can do about that.  The most important thing to remember is that this is a game, chill and enjoy it!  There will always be another mob to kill!!!</font><P><font color=cyan><b><i>Druid of the 34th Ring</i></b></font></br>
