<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/btheeliteforce.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=naroon>Naroon</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Elite Officer</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>5/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>2:58:40 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Nicely put Coatie! I wasn't at the raid but was looking over my husband Fazzar's shoulder. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  There was definitely fault on both sides of that particular situation. I know from experience, however, how hard it is to get Cara to spawn so I could sympathize with the other guild. Even when faced with upset people, we must conduct ourselves in a calm, adult manner in order to quickly resolve the problem. In the end this will only increase the reputation of the Elite Force. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#A8A8A8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uwildviene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wildviene</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Bodacious Barbarian Babe</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>123</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>5/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>8:40:51 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.3snip.com/eliteforce/images/wildbutt.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have attempted to respond several times, not happy with this entire situation.  I can flame all day and it won't change a thing.  I made several errors, neglected to call a camp check.  Honest mistake, had a LOT going on.  This in NO way excuses the other parties behavior.  Also, I did not tell my parties what I was doing... I had no intention of taking the guys key, we didn't need it, but after what he did I WAS going to make him squirm.<br>
We have had Cara taken from us half a dozen times, NOT ONCE, did we walk in screaming obsenities and calling people names.  I do not want to disagree with a guildmate but Cara is simple to have pop, the trick is getting back to her before she is killed.  So you do it again... anyone who's been in the tower as much as we have goes in EXPECTING it.<br>
<br>
Enough said, that's about as &quot;Elite&quot; as I can be on the entire matter.<br>
<br>
