</TR><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uwordaensilvershadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wordaen Silvershadow</A> at: 5/2/01 11:29:52 am</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#A8A8A8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucoatlicue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coatlicue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Guild Leader</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>174</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>5/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>12:38:05 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.3snip.com/eliteforce/images/coatie.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Word and Wild, I really do appreciate your feedback on this.  However I do want to make one point clear...<br>
<br>
I did NOT direct this post to either of you, and I am sorry if you took it that personally that you would feel hurt or &quot;betrayed&quot;.<br>
<br>
And I never once said that the other guild member(s) had any sort of excuse for how they acted.  Maybe he and the other members did not know much about this zone and about Cara or anything.  However, that is not what the main &quot;issue&quot; is.  the main issue is how we present ourselves as a guild and as &quot;resident's&quot; of Norrath.  <br>
<br>
Just because we might have more &quot;experience&quot; in a certain zone or with a certain pop, does not mean others have the same kind of knowledge or patience.  I am not excusing the other guild's behavior, please UNDERSTAND that.  The ONLY thing I request is that if something like this DOES happen again in the future, that we be the bigger man and act adult.  Just because some other punk has the bad mouth and the audacity to use foul language should not give us the O.K. to do the same.  Now, to make another point clear, NO ONE in the Elites that night used a bad word.  However, HARSH words were exchanged, and Honestly, i feel that that situation could have been avoided entirely, if only we ALL kept on track and been courteous of others in the zone.<br>
<br>
This is not necessarily about who called a camp check, who didn't or any of that.  This is not about how to make Cara pop or how easy it might be.  This is not about what has happened to us in past experiences with KSing or whatnot.  This is about how we present ourselves as a family, how patient we are, and how courteous of others we try to be, whether they deserve it or not.<br>
<br>
So put them on your list of people you refuse to help, that is completely your choice, i am not trying to disuade you from doing that. You have a right to your own opinions and own feelings, and not ONCE have I ever tried to hold any of you from keeping that to yourselves.  ALL I am asking is that we all work together to make our guild a friendly place and to show others what AWESOME people we have in the guild.<br>
<br>
Do we want to present ourselves as the kind of guild that says.. &quot;oh well she/he/it wasn't engaged so your SOL..&quot;   I hope not.  I hope that we are the type of guild that can act mature and work things out on in an adult manner and HELP each other.  REGARDLESS if the other guild deserves that or not, it's OUR duty as Elites to what?.. be Honorable.. be Courageous... be Compassionate people.<br>
<br>
Like i said, this was not directed at anyone in particular.  Wild, this was not a post to point out any mistakes you made.. god knows I have made MANY mistakes myself and I know I will continue to do so unfortunately... Word, this was not a post to flame you or to give the other guild an excuse.  This was just a request to be respectful of other players in the game.  That's IT.  That's ALL I wanted to say, obviously, some people took it personally.  <br>
<br>
*sighs*  I hope that you guys do not feel hurt or offended any longer.  I am trying my best to do all I can for the guild and to make everyone feel as comfortable as possible.  If i worded this post wrong and you feel offended still, send me an email, we'll work it out on the side, so others don't have to &quot;listen&quot; to us &quot;flame&quot; or whatnot.  Believe me, i'm not looking for an argument or anything.  but if you still have issues with this, feel free to contact me, you all know how open I am and how much I love to hear feedback from you all, regardless if it's positive or negative.<br>
<br>
*shrugs* what else can I do but to try and give feedback myself?  </font><P><IMG SRC="http://www.3snip.com/eliteforce/images/coatie-sig.gif"<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/usupajeenyus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>supajeenyus</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Newbie</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>8</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>5/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF33>12:42:13 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Raid Conduct</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I am an outsider looking in, however, I have grouped with many of you and have been friends for a long time so, for some reason, I feel the need to say something (although some of you that know me would say that I don't need a reason to feel I should say something <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
I *believe* the point that Coatie was trying to make was that whether or not the room was really &quot;camped&quot; or whether or not they claimed the camp or even whether or not the other guild was polite to you it is everyones' responsibility as an Elite to respond in a mature and reasonable manner - a manner which reflects the ideals of the guild. Sure there are going to be times when people do not live up to those ideals. I have had many occasions myself where I was ashamed of the way I reacted to something or someone within the game. Her post was a post about conduct of the Elites, not conduct of the other guild. She nor anyone else in The Elite Force has any control or really much say in the way others act within the game. That is up to the respective guild leaders and in some instances, the GMs of Verant. A case could be made in a very mature manner or it could just turn into a slap fight. I know a lot of you guys well enough to know how you would handle it and that's why I consider it a pleasure to know you all.<br>
<br>
The fact is simply this. Just as in real life, the world of norrath is filled with good people, jerks, punks, geeks, clowns and pets. Luckily, just as in the real world, we get to choose many times with whom we associate. There have been many times that I have chosen not to group with someone and it would simply be because I do not approve of their conduct. Does that make me better than them? Not necessarily - it just means our styles are incompatible. To them, cussing and swearing may be a way of life. You may say there is no excuse for their behavior. Well, there is no reason that you have to sit and take it. Unlike Real World we are lucky enough to have /ignore lists in norrath.<br>
<br>
